column1: # pl_orb: semi-major axis of the orbit (au) (in cases where not measured, it is fitted with (pl_period*24*60*60)**(2/3)/(4*PI**2/(6.67408*1e-11*(st_mass*1.98847*1e30)))**(1/3)/149597870691.0
pl_massE: mass of planet (Earth) (in cases where not measured, it is fitted assuming Earth-like density)
pl_g: gravitational acceleration of the planet
pl_teff: effective temperature of the planet (Dayside  distributed  pl_teff=st_teff*((st_rad*0.00465047)/(pl_orb))**0.5*(2/3)**0.25)
st_teff: effective temperature of the host star
st_rad: radius of the host star
st_mass: mass of the host star
pl_subT: effective temperature of the planet (Substellar no distribution pl_teff=st_teff*((st_rad*0.00465047)/(pl_orb))**0.5*(1)**0.25)
magJ: apparent magnitude of the target (J)
reference: references for parameters of the system
